  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Concerted Action by Young People (Women and Men) Community Leaders for the Strengthening of Social Cohesion and the Consolidation of Peace in Forest Guinea</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project contributes to breaking the cycle of violence that the Forest Guinea region has experienced over the past seven years. Specifically, it seeks to promote the inclusive participation of youth (men and women) community leaders in strengthening social cohesion and peace building in Forest Guinea through three main axes. Those axes are (1) inclusive and intergenerational participation of youth leaders and other community actors in the protection of human rights, conflict prevention and management, and peacebuilding; (2) support for the implementation of the existing legal framework for the fight against violence in accordance with international human rights standards in the target area; and (3) support for the socio-economic rehabilitation of young leaders through the establishment and development of community-based initiatives to strengthen social cohesion and community living.</narrative>
  </description>
